<h1><a name="begin_content"></a>Audit (A-04-09-00055)</h1>

<h2>06-04-2010<br />
Review of Medicare Part A Bad Debts at Carolinas Medical Center for the Fiscal Year Ended December 31, 2005 </h2>

<h2 class="line">Executive Summary</h2>

<p>Based on our statistical sample results, we estimated that Carolinas Medical Center (CMC) claimed $1,032,338 for bad debts that were not reimbursable under Medicare regulations.  Of this amount, $1,003,043 related to bad debts that were with a collection agency.  The remaining balance of $29,000 was unallowable for other reasons specifically related to CMC’s actions and should be adjusted on CMC’s cost report.  Finally, we identified 11 accounts with $650 in bad debt recoveries that were not reported on the cost report.</p>

